        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/32841",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=giorgiosironi",
                        "name": "giorgiosironi",
                        "displayName": "Giorgio Sironi",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Quick and dirty fix to allow the use of namespaced view helpers.\nThis works only because since view helpers cannot be in subfolders and the basename is directly appended to the path. For other classes path calculation could be wrong.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=giorgiosironi",
                        "name": "giorgiosironi",
                        "displayName": "Giorgio Sironi",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-07-22T06:34:49.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-07-22T06:34:49.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/33352",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ratius",
                        "name": "ratius",
                        "displayName": "Steven Rosato",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "The provided fix works well and does not seem to break the tests though that one must always append the \\\\ at the end of the namespace prefix for exemple in resource loading in an ini file:\n\npluginPaths[\"My\\Application\\Resource\\\\\"] = \"My\/Application\/Resource\"\n\nTo optionnally provide the ending backslash strstr($prefix, '\\\\') could be used but then again non subnamespaces would fail at that using\n\n$pluginLoader->addPrefixPath('My', 'Path\/To\/My'); \/\/My is a namespace\n\nstill the only quick solution remain but an end backslash must be provided.\n\n$pluginLoader->addPrefixPath('My\\\\', 'Path\/To\/My'); \/\/My is a namespace\n\nDon't know your thoughts on that maybe Giorgio's solution may prove the only one not breaking anything.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ratius",
                        "name": "ratius",
                        "displayName": "Steven Rosato",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-08-09T19:26:07.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-08-09T19:26:07.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/33353",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ratius",
                        "name": "ratius",
                        "displayName": "Steven Rosato",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Edit (correction): though that one must always append the \"\\ \\\"\n\n[second code snippet]:\n\nand $pluginLoader->addPrefixPath('My\\ \\', 'Path\/To\/My'); \/\/My is a namespace\n\n[with no space between the backslashes --my double backslashes were escaped] :P",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ratius",
                        "name": "ratius",
                        "displayName": "Steven Rosato",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-08-09T19:29:28.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-08-09T19:29:28.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/38332",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=at465",
                        "name": "at465",
                        "displayName": "Andy Thompson",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I also came across this issue as I'm starting to write my applications using proper namespaces. I tackled the issue using the same method. I can't see it having any problems considering \\\\ has never been used as a class name character, and looking at the end character seems the most logical way to do this.\r\n\r\nSince Zend_Loader has been modified to support PHP 5.3 namespaces in 1.10, I was hoping this could be implemented as a minor release?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=at465",
                        "name": "at465",
                        "displayName": "Andy Thompson",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-02-07T11:46:58.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-02-07T11:46:58.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/38362",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ratius",
                        "name": "ratius",
                        "displayName": "Steven Rosato",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I'm still watching and hoping for this as it is my only patch that I need to apply each time Zend upgrades. It does not break unit tests and I, too, think it should be implemented in a minor release.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ratius",
                        "name": "ratius",
                        "displayName": "Steven Rosato",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-02-08T11:20:44.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-02-08T11:20:44.000+0000"
                },
                {
